<subSubSection id="729D18B1AFD546E6878E3D575F42ACCE" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" type="notes">
<paragraph id="65217FB822E38B1AE8DE4C06CEFA81E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E770E6D60286695E5AC6190F31014D9" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">
<taxonomicName id="E4B8C28097D806BD060D01399D7685A2" authorityName="M. Nee, Kurtziana 28: 137" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum verecundum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">
<emphasis id="5A90F5F0FF0E8765264FD64C5C5D343B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Solanum verecundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="65B332BBE96EE1F697F792E748044B34" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. New records of Solanum from Colombia A Solanum tanysepalum S. Knapp (upper left corner: detail of calyx lobes; Geminata clade) B Solanum verecundum M. Nee (Brevantherum clade)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.195.78832.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/681518" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">4b</figureCitation>
) was previously known from montane forests in Peru and Ecuador (
<bibRefCitation id="89E9ED5B0B030898830FB9D0859FA01F" author="Giacomin, LL" journalOrPublisher="American Journal of Botany" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" refId="B5" refString="Giacomin, LL, 2015. Solanum L. clado Brevantherum (Solanaceae): Sistematica e Diversidade. PhD Thesis. Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Brazil." title="Solanum L. clado Brevantherum (Solanaceae): Sistematica e Diversidade. PhD Thesis. Universidade Federal de Minas Gerais, Brazil." year="2015">Giacomin 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Our new records presented here extend the distribution to Colombia to the Departments of Caldas, Quindio and Valle del Cauca (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="58BB78F1DE36CD26A648FABD5114A648" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Distribution of S. tanysepalum S. Knapp (green circles) and S. verecundum M. Nee (cyan triangles)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.195.78832.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/681519" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">5</figureCitation>
). The species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="AC8F0D235481AE377DE30AFCC3E96799" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Brevantherum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brevantherum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Brevantherum</taxonomicName>
clade and is related to the species traditionally included in section 
<taxonomicName id="0F6F7C8D996A1793E92860B0A5CA856F" authority="Brevantherum" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Brevantherum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Brevantherum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Brevantherum">Brevantherum Brevantherum</taxonomicName>
Seithe (
<bibRefCitation id="06D37303404B5A0AC71085950C663DAA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2021.107195" author="Tovar, JD" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" refId="B15" refString="Tovar, JD, Andre, T, Wahlert, G, Bohs, L, Giacomin, LL, 2021. Phylogenetics and historical biogeography of Solanum section Brevantherum (Solanaceae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 162(6): e107195. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2021.107195" title="Phylogenetics and historical biogeography of Solanum section Brevantherum (Solanaceae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 162 (6): e 107195." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.ympev.2021.107195" year="2021">Tovar et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="2D02428820711FABFEF6D8F2FC748FC0" authorityName="M. Nee, Kurtziana 28: 137" authorityYear="2000" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum verecundum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verecundum">
<emphasis id="98A3C0FAFA0F64E6DBA267C9004F1038" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="63">Solanum verecundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily recognised by the membranaceous leaves, stellate-lepidote trichomes (with partially fused rays) in both leaf surfaces and puberulous orange-coloured fruits at full maturity. More information and a complete description are available at: https://solanaceaesource.myspecies.info/solanaceae/solanum-verecundum
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
